cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below."
title: "Beyond Stochasticism: An Ontological Framework for Agentic Stability"
authors:
  - family-names: "Research"
    given-names: "BitConcepts"
repository-code: "https://github.com/BitConcepts/oea-framework-paper"
license: MIT
version: "0.4.0"
date-released: 2026-05-13
abstract: >
  The OEA (Ontology, Epistemic, Agentic) framework specifies a hypothesis-driven,
  falsification-oriented protocol for improving reliability in recursive agentic systems
  under recursive synthetic-data exposure. A bigram-proxy ablation study (12 variants,
  648 runs per variant, two domain corpora) and a two-model real LLM validation
  (distilgpt2 82M and gpt2 124M, 10 seeds x 10 iterations) demonstrate that OEA
  epistemic filtering improves mean log-probability by +1.14 to +1.61 nats, with
  an anti-calibrated control consistently degrading it by -0.80 to -0.82 nats across
  both models, confirming calibration direction as the causal mechanism.
keywords:
  - agentic ai
  - ontology
  - epistemology
  - model collapse
  - retrieval augmented generation
  - calibration
  - epistemic uncertainty
